HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1469
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor Brent Clayton of the Tennessee
Alcoholic Beverage Commission on the occasion
of his retirement.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in honoring a
distinguished law enforcement professional, who has exemplified the highest ideals of public
service and made significant contributions to the safety and welfare of the citizens of
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Brent Clayton has demonstrated unwavering dedication, professionalism,
and commitment to his fellow citizens throughout his twenty-five-year career in local and State
law enforcement; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Clayton began his storied career with the Cleveland Police Department
and worked as a detective there from 1988 to 1999; and
WHEREAS, a valuable asset to the Tennessee Alcoholic Beverage Commission (TABC)
for the past thirteen years, Mr. Clayton has served as the agency's Deputy Chief Law
Enforcement Officer since May 2019; and
WHEREAS, his leadership transcends his professional life, as his ongoing dedication to
lifelong learning has inspired his colleagues to reach for greater heights; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Clayton began his academic career at Cleveland State Community
College, from which he received an Associate of Applied Science degree in Architecture and
Criminal Justice; and
WHEREAS, at the age of fifty-four, he earned a bachelor's degree in criminal justice
from the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga, while working full-time; and
HJR1469
018020
- 1 -

WHEREAS, most recently, Mr. Clayton obtained a Master of Public Administration
degree from Tennessee State University, while helping to lead TABC through the COVID-19
pandemic and administer the agency's many new responsibilities; and
WHEREAS, outside of work, Brent Clayton is deeply rooted in family and Tennessee
pride; a native of Cleveland, he plans to return home after his fast-approaching retirement; and
WHEREAS, his many professional and personal accomplishments aside, Mr. Clayton is
most grateful for the love, respect, and companionship he shares with his wife of thirty years,
Deleana, and their adult children, Jacora, a nurse living in Colorado; Clint, an engineer with the
Tennessee Department of Transportation in Cleveland; and Brae, a school counselor in
Chattanooga; and
WHEREAS, Brent Clayton is taking a much-deserved retirement from TABC on April 30,
2026, thus concluding a remarkable career in State government; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that he be recognized for his outstanding service and dedication
to the citizens of Tennessee on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Brent Clayton, Deputy Chief Law Enforcement Officer of the
Tennessee Alcoholic Beverage Commission, on the occasion of his retirement, praise his
twenty-five years of exemplary service in law enforcement, and extend to him our best wishes
for every future success as he enjoys the fruits of his labor.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
